cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a team of mobile agents collaborating to solve a delivery problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of planning and coordination problems and proposes approximation algorithms. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing energy consumption, which is a common problem in AI. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as the paper deals with mobile agents and their movement in a graph. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with message delivery in a graph, which can be seen as a network.
